<subSubSection id="C337656CFFBAFFACFD97F9B9FCD00AE9" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9236E7FFBAFFACFD97F9B9FCD00AE9" blockId="31.[151,1437,258,2034]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FFBAFFACFD97F9B9FE8F0AB3" bold="true" box="[199,328,1938,1963]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FFBAFFACFD97F9B9FE850AB3" bold="true" box="[199,322,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The fully dark brown body, legs and antennae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FFBAFFACFE26F9B9FBA30AB2" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[886,1124,1938,1962]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersoni">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FFBAFFACFE26F9B9FBA30AB2" box="[886,1124,1938,1962]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Aptilotella andersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinguish it as the darkest member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FFBAFFACFC11F99DFE6A0AD6" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[321,429,1974,1998]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corona">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FFBAFFACFC11F99DFE6A0AD6" box="[321,429,1974,1998]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">A. corona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. This species is known from coastal cloud forest some 
<quantity id="4CD59B02FFBAFFACF9E8F99EFB380AD6" box="[1208,1279,1973,1998]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="km" value="60.0">60 km</quantity>
apart from its closest known relatives, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FFBAFFACFCFAF9F1FD9A0AEA" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[426,605,2010,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quatuorchela">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FFBAFFACFCFAF9F1FD9A0AEA" box="[426,605,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">A. quatuorchela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D64FFBAFFACFFC4F9F1FCD70AEA" authorityName="Luk &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2014" box="[660,784,2010,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Aptilotella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gloriosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAF5FFBAFFACFFC4F9F1FCD70AEA" box="[660,784,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">A. gloriosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
